At the historic Cavalier Hotel, breakfast is served daily at Becca. The Spa Omelet is a delightful option, with fluffy egg whites filled with good things like green onion, kale, spinach, and tomato, according to columnist Patrick Evans-Hylton. Goat cheese brings additional flavor, and adds a creamy texture to the dish. A wonderful potato cake is served along side, as well as toast. Mimosas always please at Becca.
Credit/Source: Patrick Evans-Hylton/For The Virginian-Pilot/For The Virginian-Pilot

Caption: At Rick's Cafe, a 24-hour diner in Oceana, breakfast is served around the clock, including a number of omelets. I selected a classic cheese omelet, simply prepared with a generous amount of pepper jack cheese melting inside. Along with the dish came side and bread options. The breakfast potatoes were a star as the side, and the pancakes never disappoint, especially in lieu of toast.
Credit/Source: Patrick Evans-Hylton/For The Virginian-Piot/For The Virginian-Pilot

Caption: The Seafood Omelette at What The Gritz is a delicious and unique take on the classic, according to columnist Patrick Evans-Hylton. Folded inside are generous amounts of shrimp and blue crab, accented with sautéed baby spinach, diced tomatoes, and crumbled feta cheese. The omelet takes on another level when a decadent, rich she crab soup is poured over top. The dish comes with a choice of side and bread; I opted for grits and toast.
Credit/Source: Patrick Evans-Hylton/For The Virginian-Pilot/For The Virginian-Pilot

Caption: The Baconator at 21st Street Seafood Company is a large omelet stuffed with chopped bacon – seven pieces in fact – and held together with ooey, gooey cheese. It's a great meat-centric breakfast dish, served with a potato side made with chopped red bliss potatoes sautéed with green bell peppers and onions. It's enough to make any breakfast goer say "I'll be back."
Credit/Source: Patrick Evans-Hylton/For The Virginian-Pilot/For The Virginian-Pilot

Caption: At The Bread Box Cafe, carefully crafted dishes at breakfast, lunch, and dinner include the Italian Omelet, a generous-sized dish full of onions, tomatoes, green bell peppers, tomatoes, cheddar, and mozzarella, giving it the flavor profile of a pizza pie. Along side is artisan bread, made in-house, and a fruit salad meticulously prepared by chef/owner Esma Terzic.
Credit/Source: Patrick Evans-Hylton/For The Virginian-Pilot/For The Virginian-Pilot

Caption: Liz's Country Kitchen has a good variety of omelets. I chose the Surf Rider, which includes ham, crab meat, diced tomatoes and melting white American and cheddar cheeses sealing everything together in a tasty, gooey way. A delicious breakfast potato casserole and fluffy biscuits came along side.

The Blue Rooster Omelet at Roosters Cafe & Grill is a delicious breakfast dish filled with tender, moist chicken folded in an omelet with mushrooms, spinach, tomatoes and tangy blue cheese. It's a tasty, healthy way to start the day when made with egg white. Creamy grits and toast come on the side.
Credit/Source: Patrick Evans-Hylton/For The Virginian-Pilot/For The Virginian-Pilot

Caption: The Spanish Omelet at Waffletown USA is simple but delicious: an omelet is filled with rich, flavorful salsa. The family-run eatery just off Shore Drive has been serving breakfast and lunch for more than 25 years. Toast and jelly comes on the side.
Credit/Source: Patrick Evans-Hylton/For The Virginian Pilot/For The Virginian-Pilot
